Title: Non-Supersymmetric Large N Gauge Theories from Type 0 Brane
  Configurations
Authors: Adi Armoni and Barak Kol
Comments: 18 pages, Latex. 2 figures. v2: refs. added, additions to the
  introduction concerning the twisted sector
Report-no: TAUP-2577-99
Journal-ref: JHEP 9907 (1999) 011
\\
  We use dyonic brane configurations of type 0 string theory to study large N
non-supersymmetric 4d gauge theories. The brane configurations define theories
similar to the supersymmetric ones which arise in type II. We find the non-SUSY
analogues of N=2 and N=1. In particular we suggest new non-SUSY CFT's and a
brane realization of a non-SUSY Seiberg duality.
